    <p>
        <strong>Hyper Coding is a</strong> systematic <strong>methodology</strong> that can be <strong>adopted _gradually_</strong> to
        improve the quality of AI-assisted development.
    </p>

    <p>It is based on five key principles:</p>

    <ol>
        <li><strong>Deterministic First</strong>: Anything that can be done deterministically should not use an LLM</li>
        <li><strong>Engineered Friction</strong>: Intentionally increase the effort required for complex solutions to make simplicity the path of least resistance.</li>
        <li><strong>Reactive Context</strong>: Automate context engineering to provide the right context at the right time</li>
        <li><strong>Tools Integration</strong>: Give your AI Agent the same external advantages you have</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time Feedback</strong>: Provide feedback to the agent as soon as possible to avoid compounding errors</li>
    </ol>

    <p>The HyperDev toolkit offers tools to help you adopt each of the principles. All under a single <code>hyper</code> CLI.</p>

